This project contains the source files, plotting scripts, and Experimental data used for 
the statistical mechanical water model: Lakshmanji Verma and Ken A. Dill, Statistical mechanical theory of liquid water, JCTC, 2025

Source code and run scripts are in Python_src folder
To run script for calculating bulk properties of water as described in the article above 
Simply run: python bulk_water_script.py  
It requires "water_functions_3D.py" and "default_parameters.py" to be in the same folder
It writes data in two folders: 
Atm_P contains atmospheric pressure and Press contains all other isobars  

analysis.py analyzes isobars from Press that generates PT_data and LLCP.
For accurate LLPT and LLCP, fine temperatue (in order of 0.1) and pressure is recommended 

Plotting scripts will require Experimental data, MD_Model_data, and there data

If you use this in your work please cite 
Lakshmanji Verma and Ken A. Dill, Statistical mechanical theory of liquid water, JCTC, 2025, https://doi.org/10.1021/acs.jctc.5c00949 
